snippet: The measure, which had been stalled for more than a decade, would stock government health centers, including those in remote rural areas, with free or subsidized birth control.
abstract: Philippines Congress passes legislation to help country's poorest women gain access to birth control; measure passes after ferocious national debate.
lead_paragraph: The measure, which had been stalled for more than a decade, would stock government health centers, including those in remote rural areas, with free or subsidized birth control.

headline.seo: Philippine Lawmakers Pass Reproductive Health Bill
headline.main: Bill to Expand Birth Control Is Approved in Philippines
headline.print_headline: Bill to Expand Birth Control Is Approved In Philippines
